<DATE>10/17/2007</DATE>
<AUTHOR>steve</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>After 6 years with my Toyota Tacoma, I felt it was time to change. After comparing the Tacoma, Frontier and Ridgeline, I went with the Ridgeline because of the ride, comfort and storage room. All three are solid bets, depending on your need. Some say the Ridgeline is not a real truck but I have had it off road with no problems. I love this truck.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Storage trunk in the bed. Two way rear door. Power sliding rear window.</FAVORITE>
